I'll go further. The name of the animal is the stoat. Not all of them live close enough to the poles to have a white winter coat. If they *do* have a white winter coat, at that point in their annual cycle they are called ermines, and are prized for their fur--both for its color and its denseness (is that a word?).  Hence the royal connection.

