My German keyboard actually has the dollar sign as shift-4. But shift-9 is the closing parenthesis (the opening one is on shift-8), and the question mark is found on shift-ß. For extra confusion, the equals sign and slash are actually shifted characters, while the plus sign is not.

Definitely an extra challenge if you use (and grew up on) a different keyboard layout.

